annotationA: V-type proton ATPase subunit B; Non-catalytic subunit of the peripheral V1 complex of vacuolar ATPase. V-ATPase is responsible for acidifying a variety of intracellular compartments in eukaryotic cells
annotationB: Vacuolar H[+] ATPase PPA1 subunit 2; Proton-transporting ATPase activity, rotational mechanism; hydrogen ion transmembrane transporter activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: ATP hydrolysis coupled proton transport; Belongs to the V-ATPase proteolipid subunit family
